## Glossary

Key terms used in this codebase:

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Shnarf | Partially computed public input that links state root hashes to L2 data commitments |
| Conflation | Grouping L2 blocks into batches |
| Batch | Group of blocks ready for proving |
| Blob | EIP-4844 data container for L1 submission |
| Aggregation | Recursive proof combining multiple proofs |
| Finalization | L1 tx that verifies proof and commits state |
| Rolling hash | Recursive hash of L2→L1 messages |
| Anchoring | The mechanism by which messaging data is placed on a destination chain to validate claiming against |
| Traces | EVM execution matrices (.lt files) |

## Repository Structure

```
contracts/           → Solidity smart contracts (L1 + L2)
coordinator/         → Kotlin orchestration service
prover/              → Go ZK proof generation
tracer/              → Java EVM trace generation
besu-plugins/        → Kotlin Besu plugins (sequencer, recovery)
sdk/                 → TypeScript SDK (ethers + viem)
postman/             → TypeScript message relay service
bridge-ui/           → Next.js bridge frontend
e2e/                 → End-to-end tests
jvm-libs/            → Shared JVM libraries (29 modules)
ts-libs/             → Shared TypeScript utilities
tracer-constraints/  → Lisp/zkASM constraint definitions
documentation/       → Centralized documentation
```

## Data Flow Summary

```
Transactions → Sequencer → Tracer → Coordinator → Prover → L1 Finalization
```

1. Sequencer produces L2 blocks
2. Tracer generates execution traces
3. Coordinator conflates blocks into batches
4. Prover generates ZK proofs (execution → compression → aggregation)
5. Coordinator submits blobs and finalizes on L1

